To close it off, If you have a goal(s) for your life … Ask yourself what that goal is without including any other person/place/thing in . 

Now, match up if the people, places,
or things you’re choosing are aligning. 

If they align now, go a little further and see for how long.

In each bittersweet example there’s something valuable. What’s valuable is in both situations there’s a goal being met. And in both situations, the person has a BACKBONE to fall on if something changes . 

(I didn’t say “backup” because that can infer “in case” mindsets.)

In this example of a dreamer: What if one thing happens? And everything changes.

Even if only ONE thing changes it’s still going to vandalize OUR ideas and unorganize OUR pre planned vision. 

However, our same dedication CAN bring the same/more fulfillment with new ideas/colors

Another example of the bittersweet roller coaster of life: 

A person who dreams of a specific lifestyle and imagines every detail a certain way. They form habits/seek the things that seem fitting. Their dedication results in them getting very close to their desires

There’s many bittersweet twists in life. 

In the marriage example: You both could feel hurt by your choice to love a person that ended up not working out for whatever meant reason. But you both also are compensated for your INVESTMENTS (what YOU put in)

Bittersweet but fair.

W/ that Being said, it’s fair to think that people choose in ways to benefit in the long run. 

(Referring back to the example on marriage): We trust our choices enough to pick a fitting partner TO BE WITH. Actual MARRIAGE guarantees our time/$ wasn’t in vain if we don’t fit.

Of course everything is ultimately taking a chance- even when the chances give us a feeling of more security. 

(Just as an example): it’s possible u can still turnout a more active coparent/partner but being married eliminates that fear by a huge percentage.

Notice I didn’t even say elated, splendid, or even happy. I just said simply content. 

Some situations & habits we entertain (out of pure or forced enjoyment)when we wouldn’t even want the basics of it at our settling age.
